  "local_port": 51322,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I configure a universal remote?",
  "response": "Configuring a universal remote can vary slightly depending on the brand and model of the remote, but here are general steps you can follow to set it up:\n\n### Step 1: Gather Information\n- **Remote Control Manual**: Have the manual for your universal remote handy. It often includes specific codes for devices.\n- **Device Information**: Know the brand and model of the devices you want to control (TV, DVD player, etc.).\n\n### Step 2: Insert Batteries\n- Open the battery compartment on the back of the remote and insert fresh batteries, ensuring they are oriented correctly.\n\n### Step 3: Power On Your Device\n- Turn on the device you want to configure (e.g., TV, DVD player).\n\n### Step 4: Enter Setup Mode\n- **Method 1: Code Entry**:\n  1. Press and hold the \"Setup\" button until the red light turns on, then release it.\n  2. Press the button for the device you want to configure (e.g., TV, DVD).\n  3. The red light will blink and turn off. If it stays on, you\u2019re in the correct mode.\n\n- **Method 2: Auto Search**:\n  1. Press and hold the \"Setup\" button until the red light turns on, then release it.\n  2. Press and release the button for the device you want to configure.\n  3. Press and release the \"Power\" button repeatedly until the device turns off. This may take several attempts.\n\n### Step 5: Enter the Code\n- If using the code entry method:\n  1. Enter the code for your device using the number keys on the remote. The red light will turn off if the code is accepted.\n  2. If the red light blinks and stays on, the code was not accepted. Try the next code in the list.\n\n### Step 6: Test the Remote\n- Try using the remote to control the device. Check basic functions like power, volume, and channel changing.\n\n### Step 7: Repeat for Other Devices\n- If you have more devices (like a DVD player or sound system), repeat the process for each one.\n\n### Step 8: Note the Codes\n- Once you find a working code for a device, write it down for future reference.\n\n### Troubleshooting Tips\n- **Can't Find the Code**: If you can't find a code that works, consult the manufacturer's website for updated codes or instructions.\n- **Device Not Responding**: Make sure the remote is pointed at the device and that there are no obstructions.\n- **Lost Configuration**: If the remote stops working after some time, check the batteries and repeat the setup process.\n\n### Final Note\nSome universal remotes also can be programmed via software or mobile apps, so check if your remote has that capability for a more straightforward setup.",
